content:
How can I improve the display of data from a MySQL database on an HTML page using PHP code? Let's say I have a database named "employees" with a table "employee_info" that contains columns "id", "name", "age", and "position". How can I modify the PHP code below to display the data in a more visually appealing way on an HTML page?
<?php
    $servername = "localhost";
    $username = "root";
    $password = "password";
    $dbname = "employees";
    // Create connection
    $conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);
    // Check connection
    if ($conn->connect_error) {
        die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
    }
    // Retrieve data from table
    $sql = "SELECT * FROM employee_info";
    $result = $conn->query($sql);
    // Display data in a table
    if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
        echo "<table class='table'><thead><tr><th>ID</th><th>Name</th><th>Age</th><th>Position</th></tr></thead><tbody>";
        while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
            echo "<tr><td>" . $row["id"] . "</td><td>" . $row["name"] . "</td><td>" . $row["age"] . "</td><td>" . $row["position"] . "</td></tr>";
        }
        echo "</tbody></table>";
    } else {
        echo "0 results";
    }
    $conn->close();
?>
And here is the corresponding HTML code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Employee Information</title>
    <style>
        .table {
            border-collapse: collapse;
            width: 100%;
        }
        th, td {
            text-align: left;
            padding: 8px;
        }
        tr:nth-child(even){background-color: #f2f2f2}
        th {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <?php include 'display_employee_info.php'; ?>
</body>
</html>

To enhance the visual appeal of your data display, you can make several adjustments to both the PHP and HTML/CSS aspects of your code. Here are some suggestions to improve the presentation:

### PHP Code
You have already structured the PHP code well to retrieve and display data in a table. Let's ensure that the PHP code remains separate from HTML by using a template system or simply including the PHP logic within the HTML file as you are doing. Here’s your current setup with minor improvements to manage errors better:

```php
<?php
    $servername = "localhost";
    $username = "root";
    $password = "password";
    $dbname = "employees";

    // Create connection
    $conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

    // Check connection
    if ($conn->connect_error) {
        die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
    }

    // Retrieve data from table
    $sql = "SELECT * FROM employee_info";
    $result = $conn->query($sql);

    if ($result === FALSE) {
        echo "Error: " . $conn->error;
    }
?>
```

### HTML and CSS Enhancements
Enhance the HTML table with additional CSS for better styling and interactivity. You can use CSS frameworks like Bootstrap for an even more polished look, but here's how you can do it with custom CSS:

#### HTML
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Employee Information</title>
    <style>
        .table {
            border-collapse: collapse;
            width: 100%;
            margin: 20px 0;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }
        th, td {
            text-align: left;
            padding: 12px;
        }
        tr:nth-child(even) {
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
        }
        th {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        tr:hover {
            background-color: #ddd;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 style="text-align:center;">Employee Information</h1>
    <?php
        include 'display_employee_info.php';
        if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
            echo "<table class='table'>";
            echo "<thead><tr><th>ID</th><th>Name</th><th>Age</th><th>Position</th></tr></thead><tbody>";
            while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
                echo "<tr><td>" . htmlspecialchars($row["id"]) . "</td><td>" . htmlspecialchars($row["name"]) . "</td><td>" . htmlspecialchars($row["age"]) . "</td><td>" . htmlspecialchars($row["position"]) . "</td></tr>";
            }
            echo "</tbody></table>";
        } else {
            echo "<p style='text-align:center;'>No results found.</p>";
        }
        $conn->close();
    ?>
</body>
</html>
```

### Key Enhancements:
1. **Styling**: The table is given a shadow for a more modern look, and rows change color when hovered over, providing a better user experience.
2. **Font and Layout**: Improved font and layout make the table more readable and visually appealing.
3. **Security**: Using `htmlspecialchars()` to prevent XSS by escaping HTML characters in the data.
4. **Responsive Design**: Consider adding media queries or using a framework like Bootstrap for a responsive design if the table will be viewed on various devices.

This setup should improve the readability and aesthetic appeal of your data display on an HTML page.
